snippet.textDisplay: No more local computing power or building pc's I guess. Just connect to the cloud. I mean if we have cloud gaming now, the possibilities are literally endless... All the big cloud players will suck up all the pc power from consumers like they do everyone's data for resale and AI development; everything will be aas subscription based or "as a service". Laptops will be thin clients and super cheap. Not to mentions IoT, so internet will be everywhere. Artificial intelligence everywhere from the cloud. The future is easy to predict now. Where do we invest our money??
